pomegranate.title: Two items records in figgy with the same identifier are not showing up as individual item records or in two viewers within the same item record in DPUL

comments.body:
Make a new ark manually for the fragment using the web form at http://ezid.cdlib.org/  -- don't fill in metadata because figgy will do that once the ark is saved. Then replace the ark for this record in figgy.

Once the identifier has been set locally on the record it won't show the one from upstream.

@kelea99 can you take a look now? The fragment got a new ark and I see it on dpul at https://dpul.princeton.edu/gutenberg/catalog/c247f117j; old one is still at https://dpul.princeton.edu/gutenberg/catalog/zw12z537v

You still see the old ark under "imported metadata" for the fragment record in figgy, but the actual / new ark is lower down on the show page.
yup! looks good, @hackmastera . both showing up. Ill do the title override and description now.  Thank you so much!

comments.body: @apferrar @faithc Can you confirm that when I search for WC063 I should end up not at search results, but instead at the collection page? I'm not seeing that use case reflected in #79 and it feels a little inconsistent and potentially surprising to me, but I'm not a common user of finding aids.

Hi @tpendragon - thanks for checking in about this. Our initial request (#79) was that the collection just show up as the first result on the search results page per the behavior of the current site; however, I do think that taking one directly to the collection makes more sense to me since that is what the user is looking to do. Taking them to a search results page seems an unnecessary step since from there they just click on the first result. Curious what @apferrar thinks.
